-- GD Power, Shenhua Energy, Xichang Electric, Zijin: China Stocks Preview
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-08-03T00:13:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/china-south-locomotive-xichang-electric-zijin-china-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may have
 unusual  price changes in China trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are as of the last close.  
 The  Shanghai Composite Index , which tracks the bigger of
China’s stock exchanges, gained 35.01, or 1.3 percent, to
2,672.52. The  CSI 300 Index  rose 1.7 percent to 2,917.27.  
 Banks: China may have had about 700 billion yuan ($103
billion) of new loans last month, the Shanghai Securities News
reported today, citing unidentified analysts. Banks extended
603.4 billion yuan in  new loans  in June, according to central
bank data compiled by Bloomberg.  
 Industrial & Commercial Bank of China Ltd.  (601398 CH),the
nation’s biggest lender, added 1.4 percent to 4.37 yuan.  China
Construction Bank Corp.  (601939 CH), the No. 2 lender, rose 1
percent to 5 yuan.  
 Coal producers: Coal at Qinhuangdao port, a Chinese
benchmark, fell for the second week. The price of coal with an
energy value of 5,500 kilocalories per kilogram dropped 0.7
percent to between 735 yuan and 745 yuan a metric ton as of
yesterday compared with a week earlier, according to data from
the China Coal Transport and Distribution Association.  
 China Shenhua Energy Co.  (601088 CH), China’s largest coal
producer, rose 1.4 percent to 24.07 yuan.  China Coal Energy Co. 
(601898 CH), the second-largest, added 1.8 percent to 10.03 yuan.  
 Metals producers: A measure of six metals traded on the
London Metal Exchange, including copper and aluminum, gained 3
percent to 3,448.6, the most since May 18.  
 Jiangxi Copper Co.  (600362 CH), China’s biggest producer,
climbed 1.6 percent to 29.89 yuan.  Aluminum Corp. of China Ltd. 
(601600 CH) was unchanged at 10.89 yuan.  
 China Railway Construction  (601186 CH): The company may
appoint Meng Fengchao as chairman of the Shanghai-listed company,
Caixin online reported, citing unidentified people familiar with
the situation. The stock gained 1.3 percent to 7.77 yuan.  
 China South Locomotive and Rolling Stock Corp.  (601766 CH):
The company secured contracts to supply train carriages to the
Chengdu and Nanchang railway departments worth 5.16 billion yuan.
The shares rose 0.4 percent to 5.42 yuan.  
 GD Power Development Co.  (600795 CH): The company said a
half-owned unit has received government approval to build two
600-megawatt power generators. The shares gained 0.8 percent to
3.60 yuan.  
 Jiangling Motors Corp.  (000550 CH): The Chinese commercial
vehicle partner with Ford Motor Co. said July vehicle sales
totaled 13,122, up from 9,829 units a year ago. The stock rose 1
percent to 24.26 yuan.  
 Rizhao Port Co.  (600017 CH): The company said first-half
net income rose 32 percent from a year earlier to 231.4 million
yuan. Its shares rose 1.4 percent to 6.69 yuan.  
 Shandong Jinling Mining Co.  (000655 CH): The company will
invest 21 million yuan to form a joint venture to manufacture
oxidized pellets. The stock gained 7.7 percent to 16.73 yuan.  
 Sichuan Xichang Electric Power Ltd.  (600505 CH): The
company posted a 91 percent drop in first-half profit to 11.2
million yuan ($1.65 million), from a year earlier. The stock
rose 1.9 percent to 9.04 yuan.  
 Taiyuan Coal Gasification Co. ’s (000968 CH): The company
said first-half net profit rose 44.6 percent to 175 million yuan
from a year earlier. Its shares rose 3.8 percent to 15.99 yuan.  
 Zijin Mining Group Co.  (601899 CH): China’s largest gold
producer said its partners agreed to extend the effective period
for an agreement to jointly purchase Platmin Congo Ltd. to Aug.
31 or later. The stock rose 1.3 percent to 6.27 yuan.  
